Reflection means
    A program can inspect and sometimes modify its own structure at runtime—things like class names, properties, functions, etc.

Reality check (important)
    Standard C++ (even up to modern standards) does NOT have full built-in reflection like Java or C#.

So in pure C++:
    You cannot ask: “what members does this class have?” at runtime
    No native metadata system

That’s why systems like Unreal Engine build their own reflection layer using macros + code generation

When is reflection useful?
    Serialization (JSON/XML)
    Game editors (like Unreal)
    UI binding
    Scripting systems
    Debug tools